This paper discusses the creation of syntactic resources using human editing of tagger and parser output, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The study also involves cognitive biases in human decision making, which could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The experiments and analysis involve statistical methods, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the study discusses the impact of the findings on future annotation efforts and parser evaluations, which could be relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
